reviews.text: Great spot for tavern style pizza. Full Italian food menu. Owner will wait your table and makes own dough and sauce. Feel free to ask him anything. Highly recommend.

One of my favorite pizza restaurants. My favorite is the BBQ chicken.  They use Sweet Bay Rays, plenty of chicken. Get the onions and garlic on the pizza. üòã The wings are awesome. They are a nice size, not sparrow wings like some places. The garlic parmesan are my favorite but the naked wings are also delicious, with or without the ranch.  Nice beer selection. Outdoor seating is available. The owner is a real nice guy. He always teases us because we never finish what we order. We order large so we have leftovers for later.üòÇ

I've walked past Angie's for the last 5 years and finally gave it a try. I'm sad I've wasted the last 5 years not ordering here! The pizza was delicious but these breadsticks really stand out. Soft, bite size, flavorful. I'll be getting these at least once a week lol

Also, they had to call me because of the order, and the person I talked to was so incredibly pleasant. 10/10
This is an old school pizza joint. Robby the owner will most likely be making your awesome amazing pizza. Try the Mike's hot honey on the pepperoni. Game changer!
Cesar salad, Sophia Loren pasta & thin crust Sicilian üçï,   what a great spot to eat & replenish while waiting for our next flight, the bruschetta is to die for as well, thank you all.

editorial_summary.overview: Longtime, old-school Italian staple featuring a full bar & TV sports in brick-lined digs.
